# Java Code Quality — Kafka Tool

## Style and conventions

- Match existing code: tabs for indentation in this project, `var` where type is obvious, static imports for constants.
- Keep classes focused; prefer extending existing abstractions (`AbstractKafkaToolStage`, `KafkaAgnosticConsumer`, `ScreenBuilder`) over new parallel patterns.
- Use SLF4J for logging (`LoggerFactory.getLogger`); no `System.out.println` in production code.
- Prefer immutable DTOs in `inspect/` (`TopicInfo`, `KafkaMessage`); mutable state belongs in services or JavaFX nodes.

## Layer boundaries

```java
// ❌ BAD — Kafka client in UI stage
var consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);

// ✅ GOOD — delegate to consumers/ or inspect/
KafkaAgnosticConsumer.json().start(broker, topic, callback);
adminService.listTopics(topics -> Platform.runLater(() -> listView.getItems().setAll(topics)));
```

- `inspect/` and `consumers/` must not import `javafx.*`.
- UI code must not construct `AdminClient` or `KafkaConsumer` directly.
- Settings changes go through `Settings.update*` methods only.

## JavaFX thread safety

```java
// ❌ BAD — UI update from executor/Kafka thread
messageTable.getItems().add(message);

// ✅ GOOD
Platform.runLater(() -> messageTable.getItems().add(message));
```

## Error handling

- Catch specific exceptions; log with context (topic name, broker, operation).
- Wrap irrecoverable consumer errors in `AgnosticConsumerException`.
- Do not swallow exceptions silently; at minimum log at ERROR level.
- Surface user-visible failures with JavaFX `Alert`, not stack traces in UI.

## Kafka API usage

- Use Kafka 4.x APIs: `DescribeTopicsResult.allTopicNames()`, not removed `all()`.
- Keep Confluent serializer config (`SCHEMA_REGISTRY_URL_CONFIG`) wired from `KafkaBroker`.
- Blocking poll loops belong on a dedicated executor, never the FX thread.

## Tests

- Add unit tests for new logic in `settings/`, `consumers/`, `inspect/`, `controls/helpers/`.
- Use JUnit 5 (`@DisplayName`, descriptive test names).
- Tests must not depend on a running Kafka broker unless explicitly an integration test (none exist today).
- Clean up `~/.kafka-tool/` in settings tests (see `SettingsTest`).

## Dependencies

- Bump library versions in `pom.xml` `<properties>` only; keep `kafka.version` and `confluent.version` compatible.
- Do not add dependencies without a clear use in the layer that needs them.

## Before finishing

- Run `mvn verify` and fix compilation/test failures.
- Avoid deprecated APIs; resolve compiler `-Xlint:deprecation` warnings when touching affected code.
